naipmoro.gramm

Interface Statement

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Assertion, Hypothesis

    public interface Statement
    An interface to cover all Metamath statements: assertions (axioms and theorems) and hypotheses (variable-type and logical).

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      String[] getBody()
      Returns the body of the statement as a (possibly empty) string array of Metamath constants and variables.
      String getKind()
      Returns the kind of statement: "$a" for axioms, "$p" for theorems, "$f" for variable-type hypotheses, or "$e" for logical hypotheses.
      String getLabel()
      Returns the identifying label of the statement.
      Mandatory getMandatory()
      Returns the Mandatory object associated with the statement.
      StatementCore getStmtCore()
      Returns the core elements of the statement, namely its type and its body.
      String getType()
      Returns the type of statement.

    • Method Detail

      • getLabel

        String getLabel()
        Returns the identifying label of the statement.
        Returns:
        the label of the statement

      • getKind

        String getKind()
        Returns the kind of statement: "$a" for axioms, "$p" for theorems, "$f" for variable-type hypotheses, or "$e" for logical hypotheses.
        Returns:
        the kind of statement

      • getType

        String getType()
        Returns the type of statement. This could be any Metamath constant string, but in practice it is usually either "wff" to represent syntactic statements or "|-" to represent assertions.
        Returns:
        a Metamath constant representing the type of statement

      • getBody

        String[] getBody()
        Returns the body of the statement as a (possibly empty) string array of Metamath constants and variables. If the statement is a variable-type hypothesis, an array of exactly one variable is returned.
        Returns:
        the body of the statement

      • getMandatory

        Mandatory getMandatory()
        Returns the Mandatory object associated with the statement. Only assertions (axioms and theorems) carry a mandatory object.
        Returns:
        a Mandatory object

      • getStmtCore

        StatementCore getStmtCore()
        Returns the core elements of the statement, namely its type and its body.
        Returns:
        the core elements of a statement: its type and its body
